# Bolão FIFA 2026 — Cursor Rules

This repo ships specialized agent definitions and project conventions. Cursor
should read these two root files for full context before answering:

- `AGENTS.md` — tool-agnostic agent spec (cross-tool source of truth)
- `CLAUDE.md` — directives doc (most of it applies regardless of the AI tool)

When the user's task matches one of the specialized agents in `.claude/agents/`,
take inspiration from that agent's expertise:

- **Frontend tasks** (anything in `src/`): read `.claude/agents/frontend.md` —
  mobile-first React/TS/Vite/PWA with strict conventions (no `100vh`, no
  `position: sticky bottom-0`, use `h-dvh` + inner scroll, etc.).
- **Backend tasks** (anything in `supabase/`): read `.claude/agents/supabase.md` —
  immutable migrations, RLS on every table, helper functions
  (`match_predictions_open`, `group_predictions_open`,
  `tournament_predictions_open`) for lock logic.
- **Scoring changes** (`src/lib/scoring.ts` or `supabase/functions/_shared/scoring.ts`):
  read `.claude/agents/scoring.md` — BOTH files must stay in sync (client preview
  ↔ server source of truth).

## Critical conventions (must follow)

- **TypeScript strict**: no implicit `any`, use `unknown` + narrowing.
- **Mobile-first**: design from 320px, tap targets ≥ 44px, `h-dvh` on root.
- **No polling**: live data via Supabase Realtime + `useRealtimeInvalidator`.
- **No client writes** to `matches`, `teams`, `scores`, `scoring_config` —
  those are server-only (Edge Functions with service role).
- **Migrations immutable** once applied to production — create new ones.
- **UI strings in pt-BR** (audience: Brazilian friends). Code, identifiers,
  commits, comments, docstrings in English.
- **Mirror user's language** in conversation. Default pt-BR; switch if they do.
- **Reuse over new code**: search `src/lib/`, `src/hooks/`, `src/components/`
  before creating a file. Common components/hooks catalog in `AGENTS.md`.

## Anti-patterns (NEVER repeat)

- ❌ `sticky bottom-0` on BottomNav (use inner scroll pattern)
- ❌ `100vh` on layout root (use `h-dvh`)
- ❌ Polling for live scores (use Realtime)
- ❌ Hardcoded scoring values (read from `scoring_config`)
- ❌ Editing applied migration (create new one)
- ❌ Importing from `src/components/ui/` into other `ui/` files
- ❌ Body-text color in `gold` (poor contrast — only icons/borders)

## Before declaring done

- `pnpm typecheck && pnpm build` must pass
- For UI changes: test on a real iPhone via `pnpm dev --host`
- Reference the `.claude/skills/mobile-audit.md` checklist for UI work
- Reference the `.claude/skills/scoring-verify.md` for scoring changes

## Output

Mirror the user's language (default pt-BR). Code and commits stay in English.
Be concise. Cite `file:line` when referencing code.
